<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 12:05AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Carson,
southeastern Hutchinson, northwestern Gray and southwestern Roberts
Counties through 100 AM CDT...
At 1205 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Skellytown, or 11 miles northwest of Pampa, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pampa and Skellytown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
